00:24:09,271 --> 00:24:11,653
and things that did qualify as relevant,

569
00:24:12,273 --> 00:24:13,674
and change how we work in the company.

570
00:24:14,889 --> 00:24:18,111
So, take you back a few slides, we had a big problem.

571
00:24:18,751 --> 00:24:22,314
The company was basically going 5X on the number of games.

572
00:24:23,135 --> 00:24:24,916
Things had to happen very quickly.

573
00:24:25,877 --> 00:24:27,378
And one of the things that happened was

574
00:24:27,518 --> 00:24:30,040
we had a big problem with how we do tracking.

575
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:31,721
The company was already doing tracking.

576
00:24:32,241 --> 00:24:33,182
It was doing it very well.

577
00:24:33,222 --> 00:24:34,963
The technology was there, architecture was there.

578
00:24:34,983 --> 00:24:36,884
It was not a problem of architecture.

579
00:24:37,325 --> 00:24:38,986
We had to change how we collect user data.

580
00:24:39,346 --> 00:24:41,928
I'm going to give you two things that we did to help that.

581
00:24:42,824 --> 00:24:45,045
The first one is what we did at social point.

582
00:24:45,085 --> 00:24:47,246
The second one, one core pack to rule them all

