00:24:49,707 --> 00:24:50,087
All right.

585
00:24:51,667 --> 00:24:52,067
Tracking.

586
00:24:52,588 --> 00:24:54,188
So how does tracking work?

587
00:24:54,248 --> 00:24:55,649
And this is true for most games.

588
00:24:55,709 --> 00:24:57,689
It's a bit of a simplification, but bear with me.

589
00:24:58,870 --> 00:24:59,830
The game has a new feature.

590
00:25:00,450 --> 00:25:01,411
Or there's a new game.

591
00:25:01,891 --> 00:25:03,111
Someone wants to release something,

592
00:25:03,151 --> 00:25:05,712
they want to do something seasonal, Halloween special.

593
00:25:06,352 --> 00:25:08,833
So we design it, we say this is design two.

594
00:25:09,527 --> 00:25:11,548
Bring in new users through virality.

595
00:25:11,608 --> 00:25:15,631
This is designed to convert or convert to a second purchase.

596
00:25:16,371 --> 00:25:17,132
Users who are buying.

597
00:25:17,192 --> 00:25:20,133
We align on a primary goal, and based on that,

598
00:25:20,173 --> 00:25:21,454
we define what we're gonna track.

599
00:25:22,495 --> 00:25:23,556
This is really important.

600
00:25:23,776 --> 00:25:26,097
What you track is a result of what you ask.

601
00:25:26,818 --> 00:25:28,319
If you don't know what you're trying to achieve,

602
00:25:28,359 --> 00:25:29,980
don't start talking about what you wanna track,

603
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:33,242
because you will fall back into collecting everything.

604
00:25:33,682 --> 00:25:35,023
If someone tells you collect everything,

605
00:25:35,043 --> 00:25:37,345
we'll sort it out later, don't.

606
00:25:37,965 --> 00:25:38,205
All right.

607
00:25:39,210 --> 00:25:41,591
I just angered half of my data people community.

608
00:25:42,171 --> 00:25:42,511
All right.

609
00:25:43,751 --> 00:25:44,472
I hope none of them are here.

610
00:25:45,512 --> 00:25:48,013
Okay, game implements the tracking.

611
00:25:48,073 --> 00:25:50,434
So we had a feature, we had a definition,

612
00:25:50,494 --> 00:25:52,455
we defined the events, then the game devs,

613
00:25:52,935 --> 00:25:55,656
every time the user buys this seasonal dragon,

614
00:25:56,276 --> 00:25:59,157
they write a row and they put that row somewhere.

615
00:25:59,177 --> 00:26:00,418
There's a file that gets sent.

616
00:26:01,038 --> 00:26:03,459
Specifically for us, it was some folder in the cloud.

617
00:26:04,269 --> 00:26:07,651
Then the data engineering team takes that group of files

618
00:26:07,691 --> 00:26:10,714
and make it into a table so the people can actually use it.

619
00:26:12,195 --> 00:26:13,275
There's a lot of ways to do this.

620
00:26:13,495 --> 00:26:14,896
That's not the goal of this conversation.

621
00:26:14,976 --> 00:26:17,098
But this was a process that we were doing.

622
00:26:17,598 --> 00:26:18,919
The problem with this process is,

623
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:20,720
everything that the game does

624
00:26:21,241 --> 00:26:22,482
has to go through data engineering.

625
00:26:23,662 --> 00:26:26,144
Every time the game team wants to have a new feature,

626
00:26:26,404 --> 00:26:28,025
a new measure, a new event,

627
00:26:28,686 --> 00:26:30,267
they have to go through data engineering,

628
00:26:30,307 --> 00:26:32,168
which is a small team and works.

629
00:26:33,588 --> 00:26:35,090
for design for five games.

630
00:26:35,890 --> 00:26:37,191
So that created a major bottleneck.

631
00:26:37,211 --> 00:26:39,053
We were actually delaying the launches of game.

632
00:26:39,093 --> 00:26:40,373
There were games that were coming out

633
00:26:41,034 --> 00:26:42,095
and not knowing what's happening.

634
00:26:42,135 --> 00:26:43,556
They had features that were being used

635
00:26:43,636 --> 00:26:44,837
and it wasn't written anywhere

636
00:26:45,317 --> 00:26:46,458
how many times it was being used

637
00:26:46,578 --> 00:26:47,679
because the tracking wasn't there.

638
00:26:48,399 --> 00:26:50,201
And my engineers were super frustrated

639
00:26:50,241 --> 00:26:51,322
because all they were doing was this,

640
00:26:51,922 --> 00:26:53,243
putting wires together.

641
00:26:53,323 --> 00:26:54,844
They had nothing that was interesting,

642
00:26:55,385 --> 00:26:56,866
no projects that had high impact.

643
00:26:56,886 --> 00:26:59,027
They were just there to configure wires.

644
00:26:59,708 --> 00:27:00,248
So we changed it.

645
00:27:01,632 --> 00:27:04,033
What we did was we implemented a change

646
00:27:04,833 --> 00:27:05,994
that I'm gonna mention in a minute,

647
00:27:06,134 --> 00:27:08,054
and I'm gonna use some tech terms,

648
00:27:08,174 --> 00:27:10,476
but what we did was we just let the games run.

649
00:27:11,376 --> 00:27:12,697
Anything that the game reports,

650
00:27:12,877 --> 00:27:14,777
any data, any event that the game collects

651
00:27:15,298 --> 00:27:16,878
is automatically exposed as a table.

652
00:27:18,145 --> 00:27:19,286
And that was very big.

653
00:27:19,346 --> 00:27:21,448
That let the games run very, very quickly,

654
00:27:21,468 --> 00:27:23,429
and it freed up the engineers.

655
00:27:23,910 --> 00:27:25,331
What we did behind the scenes,

656
00:27:25,371 --> 00:27:26,732
and if you want to hear more about this,

657
00:27:27,393 --> 00:27:29,674
it will be in the references, or you can catch up to me,

658
00:27:29,715 --> 00:27:31,076
but what we did was we implemented

659
00:27:31,776 --> 00:27:33,398
a game-specific data lake.

660
00:27:33,518 --> 00:27:36,220
We just created a database where they can get data,

661
00:27:36,420 --> 00:27:40,664
and something that parses from raw events into tables,

662
00:27:41,144 --> 00:27:42,105
which is really not hard.

663
00:27:42,145 --> 00:27:43,066
It took us about two weeks.

664
00:27:44,407 --> 00:27:44,627
Okay.

665
00:27:46,188 --> 00:27:47,408
What did we do, what did we achieve?

666
00:27:47,449 --> 00:27:48,909
We eliminated a major bottleneck.

667
00:27:49,630 --> 00:27:50,490
This is super simple.

668
00:27:50,530 --> 00:27:51,491
This is not something that's,

669
00:27:51,651 --> 00:27:53,172
we didn't implement a new patent,

670
00:27:53,212 --> 00:27:54,772
we didn't change how the cloud works.

671
00:27:55,273 --> 00:27:56,413
We just took that process,

672
00:27:57,534 --> 00:27:58,875
added some automation at the end,

673
00:27:58,935 --> 00:28:01,656
and made that very less painful.

674
00:28:02,516 --> 00:28:04,037
Games still need to develop code.

675
00:28:04,437 --> 00:28:07,419
Games still need to code tracking.

676
00:28:08,199 --> 00:28:09,760
If they want something to be recorded,

