00:30:13,544 --> 00:30:14,965
All right, based on a true story,

728
00:30:15,065 --> 00:30:17,427
we had a game that wanted to implement a bidding system

729
00:30:18,087 --> 00:30:19,749
for the programmatic bidding.

730
00:30:20,309 --> 00:30:22,271
We had a team in the company, it wasn't a game,

731
00:30:22,291 --> 00:30:23,412
but it was a team in marketing

732
00:30:23,452 --> 00:30:26,014
that wanted to develop our own bidding system.

733
00:30:27,035 --> 00:30:28,296
Then this is another example

734
00:30:28,336 --> 00:30:29,897
for don't develop what you can buy.

735
00:30:30,157 --> 00:30:31,999
This is not the core competency for the company.

736
00:30:32,039 --> 00:30:33,019
We are game developers.

737
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:34,581
All right.

738
00:30:36,863 --> 00:30:38,404
One core pack to rule them all.

739
00:30:39,578 --> 00:30:42,581
The idea behind this is we had a problem.

740
00:30:43,301 --> 00:30:44,462
I was working at Clarion.

741
00:30:44,942 --> 00:30:46,683
The main problem we had at Clarion

742
00:30:47,004 --> 00:30:47,984
had nothing to do with this.

743
00:30:48,765 --> 00:30:50,806
Clarion was switching from Facebook to mobile.

744
00:30:51,947 --> 00:30:53,408
Switching from Facebook to mobile

745
00:30:53,448 --> 00:30:56,590
basically forced us to rewrite all the data architecture.

746
00:30:57,111 --> 00:30:59,472
We had to bring in some very clever people

747
00:30:59,532 --> 00:31:00,713
with very fancy titles,

748
00:31:00,773 --> 00:31:03,655
and we had to build a big data system.

749
00:31:04,256 --> 00:31:05,757
But we saw an opportunity.

750
00:31:06,649 --> 00:31:09,691
to organize and bring some order into how we do tracking.

751
00:31:10,191 --> 00:31:12,472
And the thing that we did at Plarium

752
00:31:12,512 --> 00:31:15,153
was we sat with the studios.

753
00:31:15,313 --> 00:31:17,494
And we had studios in the Ukraine, in the US,

754
00:31:17,534 --> 00:31:18,195
in Tel Aviv.

755
00:31:18,215 --> 00:31:20,936
We even had two studios in the Ukraine

756
00:31:20,956 --> 00:31:22,857
within hours of each other, one in Simferopol

757
00:31:22,877 --> 00:31:23,617
and one in Kharkov.

758
00:31:24,158 --> 00:31:25,358
And they weren't talking to each other.

759
00:31:26,119 --> 00:31:28,460
Each of them had their own data collecting system,

760
00:31:28,540 --> 00:31:30,961
their own database, two game-specific.

761
00:31:31,841 --> 00:31:34,623
And then the GM asked, how much money did I make today?

762
00:31:34,903 --> 00:31:35,923
And that was a bit of a problem.

763
00:31:36,970 --> 00:31:39,331
All the pieces of the puzzle were basically scattered.

764
00:31:40,132 --> 00:31:42,593
So when we recreated the system at Clarion,

765
00:31:42,613 --> 00:31:46,034
what we did was we sat down with every head of studio

766
00:31:46,134 --> 00:31:48,435
and we said, okay, what happens all the time?

767
00:31:48,595 --> 00:31:50,136
What are the things that you always repeat?

768
00:31:50,936 --> 00:31:53,717
Now keep in mind, some of these games were strategies,

769
00:31:53,737 --> 00:31:55,038
some of these games were racing.

770
00:31:55,758 --> 00:31:58,719
They have very different, very distinct styles,

771
00:31:58,779 --> 00:32:00,080
but there are things that they all do.

772
00:32:00,540 --> 00:32:02,801
So some events we found are always re-implemented.

773
00:32:04,001 --> 00:32:05,482
Like login, like purchase.

774
00:32:07,807 --> 00:32:10,048
Some of the things that we saw were

