00:40:33,312 --> 00:40:36,094
And what we did was we changed how we A-B test.

988
00:40:36,534 --> 00:40:40,117
Now, I'm going to explain this in a very simple way,

989
00:40:40,197 --> 00:40:41,838
and this is something that everyone can do.

990
00:40:42,399 --> 00:40:45,261
I will mention a bit the math behind what we did.

991
00:40:46,062 --> 00:40:48,564
But in one sentence, what we did was

992
00:40:49,424 --> 00:40:50,465
we just applied what we know.

993
00:40:51,626 --> 00:40:54,188
When we did testing, instead of coming to A-B test,

994
00:40:55,094 --> 00:40:57,756
completely naive and say, okay, let's see,

995
00:40:57,976 --> 00:41:01,798
what is the likelihood of someone buying this dragon,

996
00:41:02,499 --> 00:41:05,281
of someone playing this new type of battle?

997
00:41:05,981 --> 00:41:08,022
What we did was we took what we know about users.

998
00:41:08,643 --> 00:41:10,124
We had a conversion percent that we know.

999
00:41:10,164 --> 00:41:13,886
We said, okay, given that we know users tend to convert,

1000
00:41:13,926 --> 00:41:15,327
for example, on the first session,

1001
00:41:16,508 --> 00:41:19,790
and users tend to buy the first dragon by level seven.

1002
00:41:20,430 --> 00:41:21,111
Given that,

1003
00:41:22,317 --> 00:41:22,997
What can we do?

1004
00:41:23,577 --> 00:41:26,239
And this is in statistical terms, this is a switch,

1005
00:41:26,439 --> 00:41:28,020
I apologize in advance for the Chinese.

1006
00:41:28,841 --> 00:41:30,862
It's a switch from a frequentist approach

1007
00:41:31,463 --> 00:41:32,403
to a Bayesian approach.

1008
00:41:32,763 --> 00:41:34,625
It just means given what I know,

1009
00:41:35,265 --> 00:41:36,786
what is the likelihood of something happening?

1010
00:41:37,567 --> 00:41:39,008
In business terms, what it meant was

1011
00:41:39,068 --> 00:41:42,770
we took something that took a month and a million users

1012
00:41:42,870 --> 00:41:45,132
and we made it take 1,000 users in a week.

1013
00:41:46,853 --> 00:41:48,754
It also means we took a lot of assumptions.

1014
00:41:49,893 --> 00:41:51,994
It means that when I have a new game and I say,

1015
00:41:52,054 --> 00:41:54,515
well, I know my conversion is usually mm

1016
00:41:55,175 --> 00:41:56,936
and happens on the first session,

1017
00:41:57,816 --> 00:41:59,457
I assume that game is like my other game,

1018
00:42:00,137 --> 00:42:01,338
which may or may not be the case.

1019
00:42:02,278 --> 00:42:05,459
So when you do these things, please consult an expert.

1020
00:42:06,180 --> 00:42:08,220
Okay, please make sure that you work with someone

1021
00:42:08,240 --> 00:42:10,821
who can verify or validate if this applies.

1022
00:42:11,362 --> 00:42:13,482
But if you can take your learnings and take what you know,

1023
00:42:14,363 --> 00:42:16,364
you can do A-B testing much more quickly

1024
00:42:16,404 --> 00:42:19,105
with a lot less users, significantly less.

1025
00:42:20,707 --> 00:42:21,808
So we use what we know.

1026
00:42:22,549 --> 00:42:24,431
